-- Bulls’ Derrick Rose to Miss Rest of Season After Knee Surgery
-- B y   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s
-- 2013-11-25T16:52:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-25/bulls-derrick-rose-to-miss-rest-of-season-after-knee-surgery.html
Chicago Bulls point guard  Derrick Rose  will miss the rest of the National Basketball Association
season after having knee surgery today.  The NBA’s Most Valuable Player in the 2010-11 season, Rose
tore the meniscus in his right knee last week, the team said on
its website. He averaged 15.9 points and 4.3 assists in 10 games
this season.  Rose missed all of last season while rehabilitating a torn
ligament in his left knee.  To contact the reporter on this story:
